China on Wednesday reported seven new coronavirus cases in the mainland for July 7, compared with eight cases a day earlier, the health authority said. All of the new infections were imported cases, the National Health Commission said in a statement, while the capital city of Beijing reported no new cases. There were no new deaths. As of July 7, mainland China had a total of 83 572 confirmed coronavirus cases, it said. Chinaâ€™s death toll from the coronavirus remained unchanged at 4 634.